data.title: Musicians born on June 26
data.meta_description: List of musicians who were born on June 26
data.text:
Born on June 26

Ariana Grande is born in Boca Raton, Florida. After starring on the Nickelodeon TV show Victorious, she becomes a popular singer with a huge social media presence.

Nathan Followill (drummer for Kings of Leon) is born in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, to a family that will later include younger brothers - and future bandmates - Caleb and Jared.

Country singer Gretchen Wilson is born in Pocahontas, Illinois.

Mark Decloedt (drummer for EMF) is born in Gloucester, England.

Colin Greenwood (bassist for Radiohead) is born in Oxford, England. Brother and future bandmate Jonny Greenwood is born two years later.

Terri Nunn (lead singer of Berlin) is born in Los Angeles, California.

Stef Burns, who in 2001 replaces Chris Hayes as guitarist for Huey Lewis & the News, is born in Oakland, California.

Chris Isaak is born in Stockton, California.

Mick Jones (lead guitarist, vocalist of The Clash) is born in Wandsworth, London, England.

Motown singer-songwriter Brenda Holloway is born in Atascadero, California.

R&B/jazz musician Georgie Fame is born Clive Powell in Leigh, Lancashire, England.

R&B singer Billy Davis, Jr. (of The 5th Dimension) is born in St. Louis, Missouri.

Colonel Tom Parker, the controversial talent manager who managed Elvis Presley's career, is born Andreas Cornelis van Kuijk in Breda, Netherlands.

Country-blues musician Big Bill Broonzy is born Lee Conley Bradley in Lake Dick, Arkansas.
